{"title_page": "Gamescom", "text_new": "{{distinguish|Gamercom|Game.com}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox convention\n| name = Gamescom\n| logo= Gamescom Logo.svg\n| image = Koelnmesse, Eingang Ost-0010.jpg\n| caption = The [[Koelnmesse]] (eastern entrance) where the event is annually held.\n| status = Active\n| genre = [[Video game]]s<br>[[Interactive entertainment]]\n| venue = [[Koelnmesse]]\n| location = [[Cologne]], [[North Rhine-Westphalia]]\n| coordinates = {{coord|50.94257|N|6.958976|E|type:landmark_source:frwiki}}\n| country = [[Germany]]\n| first = {{Start date and age|df=y|2009|8|19}}<ref name=\"Gamescom\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tradefairdates.com/gamescom-M696/Cologne.html|title=gamescom Cologne|publisher=Trade Fair Dates|accessdate=13 January 2016}}</ref>\n| last = {{End date and age|df=y|2019|8|20}}<ref name=\"Gamescom\"/>\n| next = {{Start date and age|df=y|2020|8|25}}<ref name=\"Gamescom\"/>\n| attendance = {{increase}} 373,000 {{small|(2019)}}<ref name=\"Gamescom\"/>\n| organizer = game \u2013 Verband der deutschen Games-Branche\n| website = {{URL|www.gamescom-cologne.com/}}\n| footnotes = \n}}\n\n'''Gamescom''' (stylized as '''gamescom''') is a [[trade fair]] for [[video game]]s held annually at the [[Koelnmesse]] in [[Cologne]], [[North Rhine-Westphalia]], [[Germany]]. Since 2018, it has been organised by ''game \u2013 Verband der deutschen Games-Branche'' (English: Association of the German video game industry); and before that, by the Bundesverband Interaktive Unterhaltungssoftware (BIU).<ref>[https://www.game.de/en/events-and-partnerships/gamescom/ game \u2013 Gamescom information]</ref> It supersedes [[Games Convention]], held in [[Leipzig]], [[Saxony]], Germany. Gamescom is used by many [[video game developer]]s to exhibit upcoming games and game-related hardware.<ref>{{cite web|title=gamescom2018: first exhibitors confirmed |url=http://news.gamescom.de/en/2018/03/gamescom2018-first-exhibitors-confirmed/ }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamezine.co.uk/news/formats/xbox360/lost-planet-2-make-ps3-debut-at-gamescom-$1318164.htm |title=Lost Planet 2 to make PS3 debut at GamesCom |date=2009-08-11 |publisher=Game Zine |accessdate=2009-08-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090815202201/http://www.gamezine.co.uk/news/formats/xbox360/lost-planet-2-make-ps3-debut-at-gamescom-$1318164.htm |archivedate=15 August 2009 |df=dmy }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://videogamesrepublic.com/?p=7999|title=Sony confirms unveiling of new Heavy Rain character for Gamescom|date=2009-08-11|publisher=Video Games Republic|accessdate=2009-08-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100131062259/http://videogamesrepublic.com/?p=7999|archive-date=31 January 2010|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/namco-bandai-partners--gamescom-line-up-tekken-6--dragon-ball--raging-blast--dragon-ball--revenge-of-king-piccolo--one-piece-unlimited-cruise-2--tales-of-symphonia-trade---dawn-of-the-new-world--family-trainer--extreme-challenge--katamari-forever-and-cham|title=Namco Bandai Partners' gamescom line-up|last=Namco Bandai Partners (Press release)|date=2009-08-07|accessdate=2009-08-11}}</ref>\n\nGamescom is the world's largest gaming event, (measured by exhibition space and number of visitors) with 370,000 visitors and 1037 exhibitors from 56 countries attending the show in 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamescom.global/news/content-for-media-representatives/press-information-of-gamescom/press-information-of-gamescom.php?aktion=pfach&p1id=kmpresse_gamescom_e&format=html&base=&tp=kme9&search=&pmid=kmeigen.kmpresse_0480_2018pm23_e&start=0&anzahl=10&channel=kmeigen&language=e&archiv=|title=Final Report Gamescom 2018|publisher=gamescom.global|accessdate=2018-05-21}}</ref> and the biggest gaming news expo of the year worldwide.\n\n==Areas==\n*Business area\n*Cosplay village\n*Entertainment area\n*Family and friends\n*Fanshop area\n\n==Events==\n===2009===\nGamescom 2009 was held from 19\u201323 August.<ref name=\"Gamescom\"/> 245,000 people attended that year's visit.<ref name=\"Gamescom\"/>\n\n==== Exhibitors ====\n{|class=\"wikitable collapsible autocollapse\"\n|-\n! colspan = \"2\" |2009 exhibitors\n|-\n|valign=top|\n'''[[2K Games]]'''\n* ''[[Mafia II]]'' <small>(360, PC, PS3)</small>\n* ''[[BioShock 2]] <small>(360, PC, PS3)</small>\n\n'''[[Activision]]'''\n* ''[[Diablo III]]'' <small>(PC, 360, PS3)</small>\n* ''[[DJ Hero]]'' <small>(360, PS2, PS3, Wii)</small>\n* ''[[Guitar Hero 5]]'' <small>(360, PS2, PS3, Wii)</small>\n* ''[[Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 2]]'' <small>(360, PC, PS3)</small>\n* ''[[StarCraft II: Wings of Liberty]]'' <small>(PC)</small>\n* ''[[Tony Hawk: Ride]]'' <small>(360, PS3, Wii)</small>\n\n'''[[Atari]]'''\n* ''[[Star Trek Online]]'' <small>(PC)</small>\n\n'''[[Capcom]]'''\n* ''[[Dark Void]]'' <small>(360, PC, PS3)</small>\n* ''[[Lost Planet 2]]'' <small>(360, PC, PS3)</small>\n* ''[[Monster Hunter Tri]]'' <small>(Wii)</small>\n* ''[[Spyborgs]]'' <small>(Wii)</small>\n\n'''[[Electronic Arts]]'''\n* ''[[Battlefield: Bad Company 2]]'' <small>(360, PC, PS3)</small>\n* ''[[Crysis 3]]'' <small>(360, PC, PS3)</small>\n* ''[[Dante's Inferno (video game)|Dante's Inferno]]'' <small>(360, PS3, PSP)</small>\n* ''[[Dragon Age: Origins]]'' <small>(360, PC, PS3)</small>\n* ''[[FIFA 10]]'' <small>(360, DS, PC, PS2, PS3, PSP, Wii)</small>\n* ''[[Mass Effect 2]]'' <small>(360, PC)</small>\n* ''[[Need for Speed: Shift]]'' <small>(360, PC, PS3, PSP)</small>\n* ''[[Spore Hero]]'' <small>(Wii)</small>\n* ''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic]]'' <small>(PC)</small>\n* ''[[The Sims 3: World Adventures]]'' <small>(PC)</small>\n\n'''[[Konami]]'''\n* ''[[Castlevania: Lords of Shadow]]'' <small>(360, PC, PS3)</small>\n* ''[[Metal Gear Solid: Peace Walker]]'' <small>(PSP)</small>\n* ''[[Pro Evolution Soccer 2010]]'' <small>(360, DS, PC, PS2, PS3, PSP, Wii)</small>\n* ''[[Silent Hill: Shattered Memories]]'' <small>(PS2