 ==\nFrom 2009 to 2016, the Game Developers Conference Europe (GDC Europe), a European spinoff of the [[Game Developers Conference]], has been held in conjunction with the Gamescom. The Conference took place at the Cologne Congress Centre East.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gdceurope.com/aboutgdc/ |title=About Game Developers Conference Europe |date=15-16 August 2016 |location=Cologne, Germany |work=[[GDC Europe]] |publisher=[[UBM Tech]] |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130124040649/http://www.gdceurope.com/aboutgdc/ |archive-date=24 January 2013 |access-date=24 August 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Electronic Entertainment Expo]]\n* [[PAX (event)]]\n* [[Brasil Game Show]]\n* [[Gamercom]]\n* [[Game Developers Conference]]\n* [[Games Convention]]\n* [[Asia Game Show]]\n* [[Paris Games Week]]\n* [[Tokyo Game Show]]\n* [[IgroMir]]\n* [[Video gaming in Germany]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2|refs=\n<ref name=\"ea_1\">\n{{Cite web |title=EA GamesCom 2009 Press Conference Video Archive |url-status=dead |url=http://www.ea.com/blogs/gamescom/gamescom-press-conference  |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100914220355/http://www.ea.com/blogs/gamescom/gamescom-press-conference |archivedate=14 September 2010}}\n</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Gamescom}}\n* {{Official website}}\n\n{{portal bar|Europe|Germany|Video games}}\n{{Video Game Trade Shows|state=expanded}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2011}}\n\n[[Category:August events]]\n[[Category:Events in Germany]]\n[[Category:Recurring events established in 2009]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Cologne]]\n[[Category:Trade fairs in Germany]]\n[[Category:Video game events]]\n[[Category:Video game trade shows]]\n[[Category:Video games in Germany]]\n", "name_user": "Dawnseeker2000", "label": "safe", "comment": "MOS:DATEUNIFY (audit)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gamescom"}
